title: For Sale/Trade:  Pistol AR  PDW  (Extar EXP 5.56) MODIFIED
postcontent:
I was looking to build the ultimate Personal Defense Weapon because I imagined what it would be like to be surrounded by a large group of protesters intent on causing me harm.
I started with a stock Extar EXP 5.56 because I wanted the shortest and lightest PDW possible. I wanted high capacity and the ability to choose between readily available bullet types and weights.
I changed out the grip because my fingers did not fit it well. I added an angled foregrip because it got pretty warm after a few magazines were run through it. I added a single point sling in the rear, but it was not comfortable to carry and it did not stabilize the weapon the way I wanted. I switched to a dual point sling and it felt perfect. I confirmed this at the range. It carries well and transitions to target beautifully. 
It is small enough to slip into a small pack and get tossed in the car for drives.
This is not a weapon to be used to put holes in paper. It is designed to be there for you in case you find yourself surrounded by the next angry mob of protesters. This PDW will give you the chance you need to get you and your family out of the worst crap this disgusting community can throw at you.
You get the modified EXP, the bag and 2 30 round Troy battle mags.
I have numerous pics I can send.
Link to shooting at the open range: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ah0c_sqjR48

SIG SAUER® introduces the SBX Pistol Stabilizing Brace, an update to the SB15 Pistol Stabilizing brace, a shooter’s aid that is designed to improve the single-handed shooting performance of buffer tube equipped pistols. title: For Sale/Trade:  JBL Studio L Series 7.1 Surround Sound System - Price Reduced
postcontent:
I realize this is not exactly armslist.com "material", however I have used this site with great success and hope you are either interested in purchasing the equipment with cash or trading with weapons/ammo.  If you are, that's great and I hope to hear from you.

I am selling my like new JBL Studio L Series 7.1 sound equipment. Included in this listing is the LC2 center channel, a pair of L820 front bookshelf speakers, 2 pair of L810 surrounds and the L8400P 12" 600 watt-RMS (1200 Peak) powered subwoofer. If you want to know all the specs, I recommend you check out JBL's website because I can't list all the features. These are JBL's top of the line residential speakers and I guarantee they will not disappoint you. I had everything connected to a Harman/Kardon AVR3600 and the sound quality was outstanding. Watching action films with explosions or chase scenes would shake the house. All the speakers match with cherry wood cabinetry, which is hard to find these days since JBL is now primarily manufacturing black cabinets.

I purchased the set new about 4 years ago, broke them in properly, used them appropriately (no block parties), then got married and had a son. The speakers and amp took up too much space, my boy always wanted to play with the amp's buttons and the system overall was too loud to watch TV while he was sleeping. So everything was disconnected and neatly stored about a year and a half ago. I recently hooked everything up for a sound check and they are still amazing. 

My price is less than half of MSRP and I feel is fair for the condition the speakers are in. I am open to cash and trade offers, as long as you are reasonable and have something I'm willing to trade for. As mentioned above, I am very open to trades for guns and ammo.  I am not particularly open to piecing the set out because they get harder to sell as things have been picked through. If you agree to purchase all the speakers at the price I am advertising, I'll give you the Harman/Kardon AVR3600 for nothing additional.  The equipment is really heavy so I'm not willing to ship it.  I am willing to exchange anywhere within a 40 mile radius of Ottawa. If you have any questions regarding the equipment or would like me to send you more photos, please feel free to contact me.  Thanks for looking.

-Drew
